[_Ehrlichia phagocytophilia_ (or _E. equi_-like agent), which causes
erlichiosis, is indeed spread by ticks of the genus _Ixodes_, which also
transmit the causative agents of Lyme borreliosis and babesiosis (a
protozoan intraerythrocytic infection). The symptoms and laboratory
abnormalities are similar to the monocytic form due to _E. chaffensis_.
This organism is also tickborne but usually spread by _Dermacentor
variabilis_ and _Amblyomma americanum_. The increase in cases in 2003 is
likely to be primarily related to increased recognition and reporting, as
noted in the article. - Mod.LL]
